description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic experienced Clinical Psychologist with experience of carrying Autism and neuropsychological assessments to have a lead role in our Child Development Psychology Team in CAMHS North Derbyshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Child Development Psychology Team (CDPT) offers neuropsychological assessments, mainly assessments of Autism with young people. The team, based in CAMHS, works closely with the Paediatricians and Speech and Language Therapists in the Division contributing to multi-disciplinary assessments. We have a good track record in this approach. The Psychologist will take a lead role in supervision for the team, service delivery, and contribute to more complex assessments, formulations and interventions. In addition to this they will have the opportunity to contribute to relevant projects and training programmes across CAMHS and Paediatrics. CDPT is part of an enthusiastic and experienced CAMHS service with great opportunities for CPD and ongoing support. The post holder will be managed and supervised by the Team Lead and Consultant Clinical Psychologist for LD CAMHS / CDC Psychology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be a qualified Clinical Psychologist, registered with HCPC and:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have significant experience in working with young people with learning disabilities and / or Autism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally have PBS training or experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally have some leadership experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have proven excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a strong commitment to multi-disciplinary working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be based within CAMHS at The Den, Chesterfield Royal Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about this post please contact Dr Penny Tunnicliffe, Clincial Psychologist, or Dr Martha Laxton-Kane, Consultant Clinical Psychologist on (01246) 514412.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about this post please contact Dr Penny Tunnicliffe, Clincial Psychologist, or Dr Martha Laxton-Kane, Consultant Clinical Psychologist on (01246) 514412.&lt;/p&gt;
